        "title": "How to resolve Maven dependency for Hibernate in NetBEans 12.4",
        "body": "<p>I'm learning Hibernate. This is my day 1 and I'm watching this video on YouTube: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vOiCGQ-DXX8&amp;list=PLsyeobzWxl7qBZtsEvp_n2A7sJs2MpF3r&amp;index=4&amp;ab_channel=Telusko\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Hibernate Tutorial | Practical<\/a>. I did exactly what the tutor said but my program is not able to recognize:<\/p>\n<pre><code>import org.hibernate.Session;\nimport org.hibernate.SessionFactory;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>It says: <strong>Package org.hibernate does not exists.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Here is my <strong>pom.xml<\/strong><\/p>\n<pre><code>...\n&lt;dependencies&gt;\n    &lt;dependency&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;mysql&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;mysql-connector-java&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;8.0.26&lt;/version&gt;\n    &lt;/dependency&gt;\n    &lt;dependency&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;org.hibernate&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;hibernate-core&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;4.1.6.Final&lt;/version&gt;\n    &lt;/dependency&gt;\n&lt;/dependencies&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Here is the screenshot:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Zya98.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Zya98.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /><\/a><\/p>\n<p>I can see <code>hibernate-core-5.5.6.Final.jar<\/code> on the left panel but when I hover on that, the tooltip says:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Dependency not yet downloaded. Build project to correct errors.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>Yes, I Clean-Build it again and again. I googled a lot but none of the answer is working. Please help.<\/p>\n",
